# Trivy Ignore File
# ==================
# This file lists CVE IDs that Trivy should ignore during vulnerability scanning.
# These are typically vulnerabilities in the base OS image (node:18-alpine) that
# have no available fix upstream, or are false positives for our use case.
#
# Each entry should be reviewed periodically and removed once a fix is available.
# Format: One CVE ID per line.
#
# Example:
# CVE-2023-XXXXX
